727419f-a.title: Queens: Metropolitan Avenue - 65th Street
727419f-a.text:
Metropolitan Avenue between 65th Street and Ft. Olivet Crescent,
showing on the south side of Metropolitan Avenue, a peayed roof house
known as the W. Powell house of 1880, H. Horuever owned it from 1873
to 1891; Christ Homeyer was the owner in 1909. This place was demolish-
ed in 1923. In the foreground of view No. 1 is a partial sight of the
Lutheran Cemetery. The brick two story is 6822 Ketropolitan Avenue.
View No. 2 sh ws a rear view of the homes mentioned in view one. In
addition on the north side of the above mentioned Avenue is seen from
left to right the Burroughs and Marshal homes.
March 1923.
Views 1 and 2
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection
